<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910628-0082</DOCNO><DOCID>910628-0082.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Oshawa Group Ltd.:   Layoff of 300 Workers Set   At Ontario Grocery Stores</HL><DATE>06/28/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2</SO><CO>   OSH.A</CO><MS>CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>FOOD RETAILERS AND WHOLESALERS, CONVENIENCE STORES (FDR)</IN><RE>CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)</RE><LP>   Oshawa Group Ltd., Toronto, said it laid off 300 full-timeworkers at its Ontario grocery store operations, representingabout 20% of the unit's full-time employees.   The workers include cashiers, stockroom staff, andcleaners. Employees will be given 12 weeks pay in lieu ofnotice, along with a severance package. Some of the workerswill be offered part-time work, the company said. It declinedto estimate the cost of the job cuts.</LP><TEXT>   Oshawa Group said there are too many stores chasingshrinking sales in Ontario, resulting in tight margins whilecosts and taxes continue to rise.   The company, with more than 16,000 full-time and part-timeemployees, supplies over 1,000 franchised food stores andoperates about 100 supermarkets and 150 drug stores acrossCanada.</TEXT></DOC>